items.name: 21c Museum Hotel, Cincinnati
items.description: A 1924 landmark turned art hotel in downtown Cincinnati, next to the Contemporary Arts Center and across the street from the Aronoff Center for the Arts.

fields.caption:
**Rooms:** 98.4


**Service:** 95.1


**Food: **95


**Location: **100


**Design: **100







The 1924 landmark Metropole Hotel survives in the restored terrazzo floor, curving staircase, arched windows, and ornate plasterwork of 21c, its every corner, from the 156 guest rooms to the nine-story solarium, a showcase for contemporary art. Much of it is playful and witty, such as the trademark four-foot yellow penguins that pop up in elevators and hallways.

Loews Minneapolis Hotel (formerly Graves 601)
items.description: Hot is not a word often associated with Minneapolis, a city that is Scandinavian in both temperament and temperature. But if the Twin Cities is your destination, this is the place to bunk. This 255-room downtown hotel blends ultramodern aesthetics (Indonesian Paldao‚Äìwood walls, Grecian marble floors) and local flavor (photographs by area artists). The result is extreme comfort in a postmodern package that ranks alongside hot spots in New York and London‚Äîbut at half the price. The icy minimalism of the common spaces suits this northern clime, but the service couldn‚Äôt be more warm: The staff‚Äôs austere charcoal-gray uniforms belie their genuine Midwestern friendliness. An in-house restaurant, Cosmos, serves hearty green market‚Äìinspired cuisine.

items.name: Iron Horse Hotel
items.description: Expect "a fun atmosphere within walking distance of the heart of Milwaukee" at this hotel in a former bedding company building that was constructed in 1907. The "very cool design" includes sleek and modern rooms with original art, club chairs that have tattoo-inspired upholstery, and custom-leather and wood headboards‚Äî"you feel like you are staying in a modern art museum." Smyth‚Äôs nightly tasting menu of "superior New Wisconsin cuisine" highlights local and seasonal ingredients. Complete with a century-old billiards table and a mirror made from a church‚Äôs stained glass, Branded Bar serves haute bar food and cocktails at its concrete bar. "This is the most masculine hotel you can imagine."

The clubhouse offers cuisine ranging from home-style sweet corn chowder to grilled breaded pork tenderloin, and views of the Pete Dye Golf Course; Ballard‚Äôs Bar serves cocktails in the atrium.
